f [[Nicetas Choniates|Niketas Choniat\u0113s]]'', trans. Harry J. Magoulias. Wayne State University Press, 1984.\n* [[John Cinnamus]], ''Deeds of John and Manuel Comnenus'', trans. Charles M. Brand. Columbia University Press, 1976.\n{{refend}}\n\n=== Secondary sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* [[Kenneth Setton|Setton, Kenneth]], ed. ''A History of the Crusades, vol. I''. University of Pennsylvania Press, 1958 ([http://digicoll.library.wisc.edu/cgi-bin/History/History-idx?type=browse&scope=HISTORY.HISTCRUSADES available online]).\n* Ferzoco, George. \"The Origin of the Second Crusade\". In Gervers (see below), and [https://web.archive.org/web/20120210073013/http://www.deremilitari.org/RESOURCES/ARTICLES/ferzoco.htm available online].\n* Gervers, Michael, ed. ''The Second Crusade and the Cistercians''. St. Martin's Press, 1992.\n* Harris, Jonathan, ''Byzantium and the Crusades'', Bloomsbury, 2nd ed., 2014. {{ISBN|978-1-78093-767-0}}\n* Phillips, Jonathan, and Martin Hoch, eds. ''The Second Crusade: Scope and Consequences''. Manchester University Press, 2001.\n* {{cite book|last= Phillips|first=Jonathan|title=The Second Crusade: Extending the Frontiers of Christendom|publisher=Yale University Press|year=2007}}\n*Villegas-Aristizabal, Lucas, 2013, \"Revisiting the Anglo-Norman Crusaders' Failed Attempt to Conquer Lisbon c. 1142\", ''Portuguese Studies'' 29:1, pp.&nbsp;7\u201320. {{doi|10.5699/portstudies.29.1.0007}} [http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/abstracts/86234839/revisiting-anglo-norman-crusaders-failed-attempt-conquer-lisbon-c-1142]\n*Villegas-Aristizabal, Lucas, 2009, \"[https://www.academia.edu/1619392 Anglo-Norman Involvement in the Conquest and Settlement of Tortosa, 1148\u20131180]\", ''Crusades'' 8, pp.&nbsp;63\u2013129. \n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commonscat|Second Crusade}}\n* [http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/sbook1k.html#The%20Second%20Crusade%20and%20Aftermath The Second Crusade and Aftermath] at the [[Internet Medieval Sourcebook]]\n\n{{Featured 