l.\n{{Clear}}Dim Lit Ed: Fed up with the cul-de-sac's low intelligence, Edd organizes a scavenger hunt, with the prize supposedly being a jawbreaker. Meanwhile, Ed and Eddy start an exotic pet scam.\nNOTE: This episode is dedicated to Shawn ''Wilfrid'' Godin.\n| LineColor = AEDFED\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 31\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 5\n| Title = Will Work for Ed\n----Ed, Ed and Away\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = [[Mike Kubat]] & Danny Antonucci\n----Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = James \"Wootie\" Wootton\n----Leah Waldron\n| Aux3 = Will Work for Food\n----Up, Up and Away\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2002|1|4}}\n| ShortSummary = Will Work for Ed: The Eds are broke so they help Rolf on his farm in order to get money for jawbreakers.\n{{Clear}}Ed, Ed and Away: The Eds try to catch a loose balloon, causing mayhem in the process.\n| LineColor = AEDFED\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 32\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 6\n| Title = X Marks the Ed\n----From Here to Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Marlowe Weisman, Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n----Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Joel Dickie\n----Leah Waldron\n| Aux3 = X Marks the Spot\n----From Here to There\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2002|1|25}}\n| ShortSummary = X Marks the Ed: Eddy gets a pimple and tries to hide it.\n{{Clear}}From Here to Ed: After a scam goes wrong, Eddy blames and declares war on Kevin.\n| LineColor = AEDFED\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 33\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 7\n| Title = Boys Will Be Eds\n----Ed or Tails\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Scott \"Diggs\" Underwood & Timothy Packford\n----James \"Wootie\" Wootton\n| Aux3 = Boys Will Be Boys\n----Head or Tails\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2002|2|15}}\n| ShortSummary = Boys Will Be Eds: As Nazz gives them a lecture for making fun of Jimmy, all the boys (except Rolf and Jimmy) develop a crush on Nazz and try to woo her.\n