 of love at all the cul-de-sac children at their school, Peach Creek Jr. High.\n| LineColor = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list|\n| EpisodeNumber = 55\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 3\n| Title = Ed, Edd n Eddy's Boo Haw Haw\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Danny Antonucci, Jono Howard & Mike Kubat\n| Aux2 = \"Big\" Jim Miller, Scott \"Diggs\" Underwood & Joel Dickie\n| Aux3 = Brew-Haw-Haw\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2005|10|28}}\n| ShortSummary = Eddy receives a map from his brother to a location known as Spook-E-Ville, where the Eds plan to go trick-or-treating.\n| LineColor = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list|\n| EpisodeNumber = 68\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 4\n| Title = The Eds are Coming, the Eds are Coming\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Rachel Connor, Mike Kubat & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = James \"Wootie\" Wootton & \"Big Jim\" Miller\n| Aux3 = The British are Coming\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2007|5|11}}\n| ShortSummary = After Jimmy has a nightmare where alien spaceships invade the cul-de-sac, he becomes convinced it will happen in real life.\n| LineColor = 000000\n}}\n}}\n\n===Television film (2009)===\n{{main|Ed, Edd n Eddy's Big Picture Show}}\n{{Episode table\n|background  = #ff9120\n|title       = 19\n|director    = 11\n|writer      = 46\n|airdate     = 12\n|airdateT    = Release date<br />(U.S.)\n|episodes    =\n{{Episode list\n|RTitle          = ''[[Ed, Edd n Eddy's Big Picture Show]]''\n|DirectedBy      = [[Danny Antonucci]]\n|WrittenBy       = Jono Howard, Mike Kubat, Rachel Connor, Stacy Warnick, and Danny Antonucci\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|11|8}}\n}}\n}}\n\n==References==\n'''General'''\n* {{cite web|title=''Ed, Edd n Eddy'', Season 1|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/ed-edd-n-eddy-season-1/id337382524|work=[[iTunes Store]]|publisher=[[Apple Inc.|Apple]]|accessdate=May 24, 2012}}\n* {{cite web|title=''Ed, Edd n Eddy'', Season 2|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/ed-edd-n-eddy-season-2/id358241134|work=iTunes Store|publisher=Apple|accessdate=May 24, 2012}}\n* {{cite web|title=''Ed, Edd n Eddy'', Season 3|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/ed-edd-n-eddy-season-3/id358242399|work=iTunes Store|publisher=Apple|accessdate=May 24, 2012}}\n* {{cite web|title=''Ed, Edd n Eddy'', Season 4|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/ed-edd-n-eddy-season-4/id385739972|work=iTunes Store|publisher=Apple|accessdate=May 24, 2012}}\n* {{cite web|title=''Ed, Edd n Eddy'', Season 5|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/ed-edd-n-eddy-season-5/id385740300|work=iTunes Store|publisher=Apple|accessdate=May 24, 2012}}\n* {{cite web|title=''Ed, Edd n Eddy's Big Picture Show''|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/ed-edd-n-eddys-big-picture-show/id337383409|work=iTunes Store|publisher=Apple|accessdate=May 24, 2012}}\n* {{cite web|title=''Ed, Edd n Eddy'' Episodes on Cartoon Network\n|url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/ed-edd-n-eddy/episodes/195628|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=June 11, 2012}}\n* {{cite web|title=''Ed, Edd n Eddy'': Episode Guide|url=http://tv.msn.com/tv/series-episodes/ed-edd-%27n-eddy/?ipp=40&si=1|work=[[MSN]]|publisher=[[Microsoft]]|accessdate=June 11, 2012|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130129042518/http://tv.msn.com/tv/series-episodes/ed-edd-'n-eddy/?ipp=40&si=1|archive-date=January 29, 2013|url-status=dead}}\n'''Specific'''\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* List of [http://www.tv.com/shows/ed-edd-n-eddy/episodes/ ''Ed, Edd n Eddy'' episodes] at [[TV.com]]\n* List of [http://epguides.com/EdEddnEddy/ ''Ed, Edd n Eddy'' episodes] at [[epguides]]\n\n{{Ed, Edd n Eddy}}\n{{featured list}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Ed, Edd N Eddy Episodes}}\n[[Category:Cartoon Network-related lists|Ed, Edd n Eddy epiosdes]]\n[[Category:Ed, Edd n Eddy episodes|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of American children's animated television series episodes|Ed, Edd n Eddy]]\n[[Category:Lists of Canadian children's animated television series episodes|Ed, Edd n Eddy]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Episode list for an animated series}}\n{{pp-semi-indef}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Ed, Edd n Eddy'' episodes}}\n[[File:EEnE Titles.jpg|250px|thumb|right|''Ed, Edd n Eddy'' title card|alt=Three odd-looking young boys, hanging upside-down in front of a purple-white background, with dark-orange-outlined light orange text saying \"Ed, Edd n Eddy\" near the bottom.]]\n''[[Ed, Edd n Eddy]]'' is a 131-episode [[cartoon series|animated]] [[television comedy|comedy]] television series created by [[Danny Antonucci]] and produced by Canada-based [[a.k.a. Cartoon]]. The series debuted on [[Cartoon Network]] in the United States on January 4, 1999, and ended on November 8, 2009, with the film ''[[Ed, Edd n Eddy's Big Picture Show]]''.<ref name=\"BigPS\"/> The series was originally planned to air for four seasons, but Cartoon Network ordered two additional seasons, four specials, and a film<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.awn.com/news/television/cartoon-net-greenlights-26-new-ed-edd-n-eddys|title=Cartoon Network Greenlights 26 New Ed, Edd n Eddys|accessdate=July 30, 2012|date=June 15, 2004|work=Animation World Network|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215014903/http://www.awn.com/news/television/cartoon-net-greenlights-26-new-ed-edd-n-eddys|archive-date=December 15, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> as a result of its popularity, for a total of 135 stories.<ref>{{cite web|first=Jack|last=DeVries|url=http://ds.ign.com/articles/832/832077p1.html|title=Ed, Edd 'n Eddy: Scam of the Century Review|accessdate=July 30, 2012|date=November 1, 2007|work=[[IGN]]|publisher=[[News Corporation (1980\u20132013)|News Corporation]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120627023041/http://ds.ign.com/articles/832/832077p1.html|archive-date=June 27, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> The series revolves around three adolescent boys collectively known as \"the Eds\", who live in a suburban [[cul-de-sac]]. Unofficially led by Eddy, the Eds constantly try to scam the fellow cul-de-sac children in order to purchase [[jawbreakers]]. The Eds' plans usually fail and leave them in various predicaments.\n\nFeeling confined to gross and edgy work, such as his previous series ''[[The Brothers Grunt]]'', artist Danny Antonucci decided to produce an animated children's television show similar to classic cartoons from the 1940s to the 1970s.<ref name=\"Season1DVD\">{{cite video|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000GETU2E|people=[[Danny Antonucci]]|year=October 10, 2006|title=Ed, Edd n Eddy: The Complete First Season\u2014''Interview with the Creator''|time=0:22\u20132:34|format=DVD|publisher=[[Warner Home Video]]|access-date=September 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061116200256/http://www.amazon.com/dp/B000GETU2E|archive-date=November 16, 2006|url-status=live}}</ref> Antonucci spent months designing the show before trying to sell it to [[Nickelodeon]] and Cartoon Network. Both studios reacted enthusiastically and wanted to see more but demanded [[Artistic control|creative control]], which Antonucci refused. Cartoon Network commissioned the show after they agreed to let Antonucci go in his own direction.<ref name=\"Season1DVD\"/> The first two seasons were released on DVD in 2006 and 2007. Two DVD volumes were also released: ''Edifying Ed-Ventures'' on May 10, 2005, in [[DVD region code#DVD region codes and countries|Region 1]] and in Region 2 on May 16, 2006,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0007MSU2G|title=Ed, Edd 'n' Eddy&nbsp;\u2013 Season 1, Vol. 1 (1999)|asin=B0007MSU2G}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000B7KXCC|title=Ed, Edd And Eddy&nbsp;\u2014 Volume 1 Edifying Ed-ventures [DVD]|asin=B000B7KXCC|asin-tld=co.uk|publisher=Amazon.co.uk}}</ref> and ''Fools' Par-Ed-Ise'' on March 31, 2006, in Region 1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000CQM4II|title=Ed, Edd 'n' Eddy, Vol. 2&nbsp;\u2013 Fools Par-Ed-Ise (1999)|asin=B000CQM4II}}</ref> Selected episodes were featured in Cartoon Network compilation DVDs.<ref>\n* ''Cartoon Network Halloween Volume 1: 9 Creepy Capers'' (August 10, 2004)\u2014\"Dawn of the Eds\"\n* ''Cartoon Network Christmas Volume 1: Yuletide Follies'' (October 5, 2004)\u2014\"Fa La-La-La-La Ed\"\n* ''Cartoon Network Halloween Volume 2: Grossest Halloween Ever'' (August 9, 2005)\u2014\"Honor Thy Ed\"\n* ''Cartoon Network Christmas Volume 2: Christmas Rocks'' (October 4, 2005)\u2014\"Jingle Jingle Jangle\"\n* ''Cartoon Network Halloween Volume 3: Sweet Sweet Fear'' (September 12, 2006)\u2014\"Don't Rain On My Ed\"\n* ''Cartoon Network Christmas Volume 3'' (October 3, 2006)\u2014\"In Like Ed\"</ref> The first five seasons, in addition to the ''Big Picture Show'' film are available for download on the [[iTunes Store]]. The [[Halloween]] special \"Ed, Edd n Eddy's Boo Haw Haw\" is available as part of \"Cartoon Network's Super Scary Showcase\" on the iTunes Store, but only to the UK.<ref name=\"iTunesScary\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/tv-season/cartoon-networks-super-scary/id333475193|title=Cartoon Network's Super Scary Showcase|work=[[iTunes Store]]|publisher=[[Apple Inc.|Apple]]|accessdate=January 5, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140616180504/https://itunes.apple.com/gb/tv-season/cartoon-networks-super-scary/id333475193|archive-date=June 16, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> The complete first and second season DVDs can be rented from [[Netflix]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dvd.netflix.com/Movie/70155576|title=Ed, Edd n Eddy|publisher=[[Netflix]] (DVDs)|accessdate=August 26, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140827070623/http://dvd.netflix.com/Movie/70155576|archive-date=August 27, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> while the third season and the fourth season can be streamed from the same service.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.netflix.com/WiMovie/70155576|title=Ed, Edd n Eddy|publisher=[[Netflix]]|accessdate=August 24, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Chris|last=Crum|url=http://www.webpronews.com/heres-whats-about-to-hit-netflix-you-will-lose-2014-03|title=Here's What's About To Hit Netflix (You Will Lose)|publisher=WebProNews|date=March 28, 2014|accessdate=August 25, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140826115323/http://www.webpronews.com/heres-whats-about-to-hit-netflix-you-will-lose-2014-03|archive-date=2014-08-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> The third season can be downloaded from the [[Google Play]] store and [[Amazon.com]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/tv/show/Ed_Edd_n_Eddy |title=Ed, Edd n Eddy |work=[[Google Play]] |accessdate=August 29, 2013 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00APA9CYU/|title=Ed, Edd n Eddy Season 3|asin=B00APA9CYU|access-date=2017-09-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018121543/https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00APA9CYU|archive-date=2016-10-18|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n''Ed, Edd n Eddy'' received generally positive reviews from critics.<ref name=\"AnimationWorldMagazine2\">{{cite news|first=Matt|last=Shumway|author2=Wayne, Lamont|title=Ed, Edd n Eddy: A Unique Approach|volume=4|date=June 1999|url=http://www.awn.com/mag/issue4.03/4.03pages/SCAD_EEE.php3|work=Animation World Magazine|issue=3|accessdate=July 31, 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080724032750/http://www.awn.com/mag/issue4.03/4.03pages/SCAD_EEE.php3|archivedate=July 24, 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"DVDTalk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/28046/ed-edd-n-eddy-the-complete-second-season/|title=DVD Talk Review: Ed, Edd 'n' Eddy&nbsp;\u2014 The Complete Second Season|accessdate=July 31, 2008|last=Cornelius|first=David|date=April 24, 2007|work=[[DVD Talk]]|publisher=[[Internet Brands]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090206102052/http://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/28046/ed-edd-n-eddy-the-complete-second-season/|archive-date=February 6, 2009|url-status=live}}</ref> Viewed from 31 million households worldwide in 29 different countries, ''Ed, Edd n Eddy'' was popular among both younger and older viewers.<ref name=\"BigPS\">{{cite news|first=Matt|last=Kapko|title=Ed, Edd 'n Eddy's Big Picture Show Premiers in the U.S.|date=November 16, 2009|url=http://www.awn.com/news/television/ed-edd-n-eddy-s-big-picture-show-premiers-us|work=[[Animation World Network]]|accessdate=April 30, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100207034938/http://www.awn.com/news/television/ed-edd-n-eddy-s-big-picture-show-premiers-us|archive-date=February 7, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref> During its run, the series won a [[National Cartoonists Society#Reuben Award|Reuben Award]],<ref>{{cite journal|title=Animation World News: Awards|url=http://www.awn.com/mag/issue4.03/4.03pages/4.03awards.php3|journal=[[Animation World Network|Animation World Magazine]]|volume=4|issue=3|accessdate=April 30, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215012239/http://www.awn.com/mag/issue4.03/4.03pages/4.03awards.php3|archivedate=December 15, 2013}}</ref> two [[Leo Awards]] and a [[Society of Composers, Authors and Music Publishers of Canada|SOCAN Award]] out of a total of 11 award nominations,<ref>{{cite web|title=2000 Winners|url=http://www.leoawards.com/2012/2000_winners.html|work=[[Leo Awards]]|accessdate=May 2, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120524145418/http://www.leoawards.com/2012/2000_winners.html|archive-date=May 24, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leoawards.com/2012/2005_winners.html|title=2005 Winners|work=Leo Awards|accessdate=May 2, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120524145229/http://www.leoawards.com/2012/2005_winners.html|archive-date=May 24, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.socan.ca/jsp/en/pub/about_socan/Tor20_AnnualWinList.jsp |title=20th Annual SOCAN Awards Toronto 2009 - Winners List |publisher=[[Society of Composers, Authors and Music Publishers of Canada]] |accessdate=January 3, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120222073147/http://www.socan.ca/jsp/en/pub/about_socan/Tor20_AnnualWinList.jsp |archivedate=February 22, 2012 }}</ref> which include one Reuben Award, six Leo Awards,<ref>{{cite web|archivedate=August 3, 2001|url=http://www.leoawards.com/nominees_winners.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010803004410/http://www.leoawards.com/nominees_winners.html|title=List of Nominees and Winners|work=Leo Awards|accessdate=May 2, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|archivedate=August 22, 2004|url=http://www.leoawards.com/index.php?page=nom&cat=9|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040822003218/http://www.leoawards.com/index.php?page=nom&cat=9|title=Leo Awards 2004 Nominees&nbsp;\u2013 Animation Program or Series|work=Leo Awards|accessdate=May 2, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|archivedate=October 17, 2006|url=http://www.leoawards.com/index.php?module=pagemaster&PAGE_user_op=view_page&PAGE_id=35|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061017054106/http://www.leoawards.com/index.php?module=pagemaster&PAGE_user_op=view_page&PAGE_id=35|title=Animation Program or Series|work=Leo Awards|accessdate=May 2, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leoawards.com/2007/nominees_2007.html|title=Nominees 2007|work=Leo Awards|accessdate=May 2, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080423232721/http://www.leoawards.com/2007/nominees_2007.html|archive-date=April 23, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref> one [[Annie Award]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Legacy: 29th Annual Annie Award Nominees and Winners (2001)|url=http://annieawards.org/29thwinners.html|work=[[Annie Award]]s|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313093521/http://annieawards.org/29thwinners.html|archivedate=March 13, 2012}}</ref> two [[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]] and the SOCAN Award.<ref>{{cite web|date=February 8, 2005 |url=http://www.nickkcapress.com/2005KCA/hostnomsrelease.php |title=2005 Nickelodeon Host/Nominees Release |work=[[Nickelodeon]] |publisher=[[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]] |accessdate=May 5, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120905045100/http://www.nickkcapress.com/2005KCA/hostnomsrelease.php |archivedate=September 5, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=February 7, 2008|url=http://www.nickkcapress.com/2008KCA/nominees.php|title=2008 Host & Nominees Release|work=Nickelodeon|publisher=Viacom|accessdate=May 5, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120427021724/http://www.nickkcapress.com/2008KCA/nominees.php|archive-date=April 27, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> It remains the longest-running original Cartoon Network series and Canadian-made animated series to date.<ref name=\"BigPS\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=CN/D3 Unleash New Ed, Edd n Eddy Game|author=Grove, Chris|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/article/6990|date=June 15, 2007|work=[[Animation Magazine]]|accessdate=May 26, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012115044/http://www.animationmagazine.net/article/6990|archive-date=October 12, 2007|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Series overview==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n\n| color1 = #f8d08a\n| link1 = <includeonly>List of Ed, Edd n Eddy episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (1999)\n| episodes1 = 13\n| start1 = January 4, 1999\n| end1 = June 11, 1999\n\n| color2 = #ae8efe\n| link2 = <includeonly>List of Ed, Edd n Eddy episodes</includeonly>#Season 2 (1999\u20132000)\n| episodes2 = 13\n| start2 = November 26, 1999\n| end2 = December 22, 2000\n\n| color3 = #AEDFED\n| link3 = <includeonly>List of Ed, Edd n Eddy episodes</includeonly>#Season 3 (2001\u201302)\n| episodes3 = 13\n| start3 = April 6, 2001\n| end3 = July 12, 2002\n\n| color4 = #CED31E\n| link4 = <includeonly>List of Ed, Edd n Eddy episodes</includeonly>#Season 4 (2002\u201304)\n| episodes4 = 13\n| start4 = September 27, 2002\n| end4 = November 5, 2004\n\n| color5 = #ff6861\n| link5 = <includeonly>List of Ed, Edd n Eddy episodes</includeonly>#Season 5 (2005\u201307)\n| episodes5 = 12\n| start5 = November 4, 2005\n| end5 = April 28, 2007\n\n| color6 = #B8B8B8\n| link6 = <includeonly>List of Ed, Edd n Eddy episodes</includeonly>#Season 6 (2008)\n| episodes6 = 1\n| start6 = June 29, 2008\n| end6 = start\n\n| color7S = #000000\n| link7S = <includeonly>List of Ed, Edd n Eddy episodes</includeonly>#Specials\n| linkT7S = Specials\n| episodes7S = 4\n| start7S = December 3, 2004\n| end7S = May 11, 2007\n\n| color8S = #ff9120\n| link8S = <includeonly>List of Ed, Edd n Eddy episodes</includeonly>#Television film (2009)\n| linkT8S = Television film\n| start8S = November 8, 2009\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Episodes==\n===Season 1 (1999)===\n{{main|Ed, Edd n Eddy (season 1)}}\n{{:Ed, Edd n Eddy (season 1)}}\n\n===Season 2 (1999\u20132000)===\n{{Main|Ed, Edd n Eddy (season 2)}}\n{{:Ed, Edd n Eddy (season 2)}}\n\n===Season 3 (2001\u201302)===\n{{Episode table|overall=|season=|background=#AEDFED|title=|director=|writer=|aux2=|aux2T=Storyboard by|aux3=|aux3T=Title Reference|airdate=|airdateR=<ref name=\"iTunes3\">{{cite web|title=Ed, Edd n Eddy, Season 3|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/ed-edd-n-eddy-season-3/id358242399|work=[[iTunes Store]]|publisher=[[Apple Inc.|Apple]]|accessdate=August 24, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304103311/https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/ed-edd-n-eddy-season-3/id358242399|archive-date=March 4, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>|episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 27\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 1\n| Title = Wish You Were Ed\n----Momma's Little Ed\n| DirectedBy = [[Danny Antonucci]]\n| WrittenBy = [[Jono Howard]] & Danny Antonucci\n----Marlowe Weisman, Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = James \"Wootie\" Wootton\n----Leah Waldron\n| Aux3 = Wish You Were Here\n----Momma's Little Boy/Girl\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2001|4|6}}\n| ShortSummary = Wish You Were Ed: Rolf grows tired of the modern life in the cul-de-sac and longs for the Old Village, so Eddy creates a makeshift village to scam Rolf.\n{{Clear}}Momma's Little Ed: Ed and Eddy create chores on forged sticky notes to prank Edd.\n| LineColor = AEDFED\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 28\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 2\n| Title = Once Upon an Ed\n----For Your Ed Only\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Joel Dickie\n----Timothy Packford\n| Aux3 = Once Upon a Time\n----For Your Eyes Only\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2001|5|25}}\n| ShortSummary = Once Upon an Ed: Jonny and Plank are ready for bed, only to discover that the Eds are somehow trapped in Jonny's wall. The Eds have three different stories to tell, none of which agree.\n{{Clear}}For Your Ed Only: After destroying Sarah's room, the Eds come across her diary and Eddy reads it while the kids look for it.\n| LineColor = AEDFED\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 29\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 3\n| Title = It Came from Outer Ed\n----3 Squares and an Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = \"Big\" Jim Miller\n----Joel Dickie\n| Aux3 = It Came from Outer Space\n----3 Square Meals and a Bed\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2001|10|19}}\n| ShortSummary = It Came from Outer Ed: Ed recreates a scam from one of his comic books.\n{{Clear}}3 Squares and an Ed: When Edd and Eddy discover that Ed has been grounded, they try to bail him out without Sarah and Jimmy knowing, but fail.\n| LineColor = AEDFED\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 30\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 4\n| Title = Dueling Eds\n----Dim Lit Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = John Mein, Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n----Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Scott \"Diggs\" Underwood\n----[[Rob Boutilier]] & Vern Marcus\n| Aux3 = Dueling Banjos\n----Dim Lit Bulb\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2001|12|14}}\n| ShortSummary = Dueling Eds: After Eddy unintentionally offends Rolf, the latter challenges the former to a duel.\n{{Clear}}Dim Lit Ed: Fed up with the cul-de-sac's low intelligence, Edd 