e Ed: Eddy makes Ed hide his secret magazines from his mother. Ed loses them so they try looking for them, with Eddy seeing Ed and Edd as suspects.\n{{Clear}}Ed... Pass It on...: After Eddy's restaurant scam fails, Eddy decides to start a rumor about his older brother coming home that eventually gets out of hand.\n| LineColor = AEDFED\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 37\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 11\n| Title = Brother, Can You Spare an Ed?\n----The Day the Ed Stood Still\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n----Mike Kubat & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Timothy Packford & Kent Webb\n----Todd Demong & Werner Marcus\n| Aux3 = Brother, Can You Spare a Dime?\n----The Day the Earth Stood Still\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2002|6|28}}\n| ShortSummary = Brother, Can You Spare an Ed?: Sarah gives Ed her allowance to go and buy fudge, but Eddy pressures Ed into buying jawbreakers for the three of them instead. To pay Sarah back, the Eds conduct a scam involving a pi\u00f1ata and a wedgie.\n{{Clear}}The Day the Ed Stood Still: When Edd and Eddy dress Ed as a monster, he is convinced he's an actual monster, wreaking havoc and terrorizing everyone in sight.\n| LineColor = AEDFED\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 38\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 12\n| Title = An Ed in the Bush\n----See No Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Mike Kubat, [[Jono Howard]] & Danny Antonucci\n----Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = \"Big\" Jim Miller\n----Scott \"Diggs\" Underwood & Timothy Packford\n| Aux3 = A Snake in the Bush\n----See No Evil\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2002|7|5}}\n| ShortSummary = An Ed in the Bush: Rolf and The Urban Rangers set off to camp in the nearby woods, where Eddy seeks to scare them in an effort to damage their reputation.\n{{Clear}}See No Ed: The kids are in the lane when they learn from each other that they haven't seen the Eds all day. They look for them, but no luck. Kevin becomes paranoid and suspicious, and tries to convince everyone it is another nefarious plot by the Eds.\n| LineColor = AEDFED\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 39\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 13\n| Title = Is There an Ed in the House?\n----An Ed is Born\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n----[[Geoff Berner]] & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Leah Waldron\n----James \"Wootie\" Wootton\n| Aux3 = Is There a Doctor in the House?\n----A Star is Born\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2002|7|12}}\n| ShortSummary = Is There an Ed in the House?: The Eds are \"taking a picture\" of Rolf in their latest scam when they find out that Sarah is sick. Ed and Jimmy both do what they can to take care of her and nurse her back to health, which starts a rivalry between them.\n{{Clear}}An Ed is Born: After Eddy receives baby items from his brother in the mail, he and the other Eds make a home movie to show how mature and popular he is.\n| LineColor = AEDFED\n}}\n}}\n\n===Season 4 (2002\u201304)===\n{{Episode table|overall=|season=|background=#CED31E|title=|director=|writer=|airdate=|airdateR=<ref name=\"iTunes4\">{{cite web|title=Ed, Edd n Eddy, Season 4|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/ed-edd-n-eddy-season-4/id385739972|work=[[iTunes Store]]|publisher=[[Apple Inc.|Apple]]|accessdate=August 25, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304003436/https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/ed-edd-n-eddy-season-4/id385739972|archive-date=March 4, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>|aux2=|aux2T=Storyboard by|aux3=|aux3T=Title Reference|episodes=\n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 40\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 1\n| Title = If It Smells Like an Ed\n| DirectedBy = [[Danny Antonucci]]\n| WrittenBy = Geoff Berner, Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = James \"Wootie\" Wootton\n| Aux3 = If It Smells Like a Rat\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2002|9|27}}\n| ShortSummary = When Eddy gives Jimmy a wedgie and humiliates him, the Eds are suddenly framed for various misdeeds, so the trio set off to 