arlie Chien & Julian Lawrence\n| Aux3 = Man Overboard\n----One of Those Days\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2003|8|24}}\n| ShortSummary = Ed Overboard: After a makeover prank gives May the blues, her sisters decide to cheer her up by kidnapping Ed. Edd and Eddy turn to the Urban Rangers to save Ed.\n{{Clear}}One of Those Eds: Eddy finds a quarter mysteriously stuck to the sidewalk, but soon it becomes a free-for-all, as the other kids begin to fight over it, only to all be unsuccessful at picking it up off the ground.\n| LineColor = CED31E\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 44\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 5\n| Title = They Call Him Mr. Ed\n----For the Ed, by the Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Mike Kubat & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Timothy Packford & Kent Webb\n----Leah Waldron\n| Aux3 = They Call Him Mr. Tibbs\n----For the People, by the People\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2003|11|10}}\n| ShortSummary = They Call Him Mr. Ed: Eddy starts his own company as part of a scheme to help himself and his friends move \"up\" in the world.\n{{Clear}}For the Ed, by the Ed: After rescuing Jimmy from the Kankers and a centipede, Plank is praised as the \"King of the Cul-de-sac\". Eddy challenges Plank to an election, using his scheming ways to win.\n| LineColor = CED31E\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 45\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 6\n| Title = Little Ed Blue\n----A Twist of Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Timothy Packford & Kent Webb\n----[[wikt:tout le monde|Tout Le Monde]]\n| Aux3 = Little Boy Blue\n----A Twist of Fate\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2003|11|17}}\n| ShortSummary = Little Ed Blue: Ed is in a bad mood so Edd and Eddy try to cheer him up.\n{{Clear}}A Twist of Ed: Edd and the other Eds try to use [[reverse psychology]] to ward off the Kankers.\n| LineColor = CED31E\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 46\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 7\n| Title = Your Ed Here\n----The Good Ol' Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Leah Waldron & Timothy Packford\n----Scott \"Diggs\" Underwood\n| Aux3 = Your Name/Signature Here\n----The Good Ol' Days\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2004|1|23}}\n| ShortSummary = Your Ed Here: After finding Eddy's wallet, Kevin begins to blackmail Eddy after learning his middle name is \"Skipper\".\n{{Clear}}The Good Ol' Ed: The Eds make a time capsule and find trinkets that remind them of scams both familiar and not-so-familiar.\n| LineColor = CED31E\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 47\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 8\n| Title = Thick as an Ed\n----Sorry, Wrong Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n----Geoff Berner & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Tout Le Monde\n----James \"Wootie\" Wootton\n| Aux3 = Thick as a Brick\n----Sorry, Wrong Number\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2004|1|30}}\n| ShortSummary = Thick as an Ed: Ed's 57-day-old \"lucky\" cheese chunk hinders Edd and Eddy from their latest scam.\n{{Clear}}Sorry, Wrong Ed: Rolf buries a phone that appears to be cursed; Eddy finds the phone to be stylish, so he takes it without Rolf knowing. Every time Eddy answers it, he is plagued by unfortunate mishaps.\n| LineColor = CED31E\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 48\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 9\n| Title = Robbin' Ed\n----A Case of Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Mike Kubat & Danny Antonucci\n----Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = James \"Wootie\" Wootton\n----Leah Waldron\n| Aux3 = Robin Hood\n----A Case of (Blank)\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2004|2|6}}\n| ShortSummary = Robbin' Ed: When a mysterious superhero named Captain Melonhead (a thinly-disguised Jonny, with Plank as his sidekick, \"Splinter the WonderWood\") steals the money back and returns it to the kids of the cul-de-sac, Eddy thinks it is payback time, and transforms himself, Edd, and Ed into the supervillain Professor Scam and his henchmen, the Cents, respectively.\n{{Clear}}A Case of Ed: Ed and Eddy trick Edd into believing he has a terminal illness, while taunting a grounded Kevin. It's up to Edd and Kevin to give those two a taste of their own medicine.\n| LineColor = CED31E\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 49\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 10\n| Title = Stiff Upper Ed\n----Here's Mud in Your Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Geoff Berner & Danny Antonucci\n----Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Tout Le Monde\n| Aux3 = Stiff Upper Lip\n----Here's Mud in Your Eye\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2004|2|13}}\n| ShortSummary = Stiff Upper Ed: When Sarah and Jimmy start a \"Rich Club\" in Ed's backyard, inviting everyone except the Eds, Eddy tries to prove he has got what it takes to be a member.\n{{Clear}}Here's Mud in Your Ed: Jimmy suffers a bad day, worsened by Eddy when he's scammed out of his last quarter. He eventually turns to Rolf, and the two team up to turn the tables on Eddy by pulling a con on him.\n| LineColor = CED31E\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 50\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 11\n| Title = Stuck in Ed\n----Postcards from the Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Jono Howard & Danny Antonucci\n| Aux2 = Leah Waldron\n----Tout Le Monde\n| Aux3 = Stuck in Mud\n----Postcards from the Edge\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2004|2|20}}\n| ShortSummary = Stuck in Ed: After Kevin makes a mint selling his surplus jawbreakers, Eddy tries to con some of it out of him, only to find he is completely tapped for scam ideas. Eddy ends up turning to his old disciple, Jimmy for an idea.\n{{Clear}}Postcards from the Ed: When Plank's \"parents\" come to town, Ed irritates Eddy by offering to show them around the cul-de-sac, but then Eddy gets the idea to take them on his own, significantly pricier tour.\n{{Clear}}\n| LineColor = CED31E\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 51\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 12\n| Title = Run for Your Ed\n----Hand Me Down Ed\n| DirectedBy = Danny Antonucci\n| WrittenBy = Mike